CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 26, 1941, pg. 16 reads: "In Kennywood Bike Race - Frank Schenck, outstanding Negro bicycle racer in Pittsburgh, who will ride in East Liberty Community Outing races at Kennywood Park next Tuesday. Schenck has competed in many of the major races in this section and has made an outstanding record.  He will ride the famous Schwinn-Built Bicycle, which he also sells. -Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Bicycle racer Frank Schenck, seated on Schwinn racing bike in front of bicycle shop
